cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel approach for learning semantic attributes of multivariate time-series data and using them for reconstruction and clustering of unseen classes. This involves techniques from machine learning (dictionary learning, clustering) and computer vision (feature space). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
